One advantage of Catch is that you can use native C++ expressions in your assertions, so instead of<p><pre><code>  AssertThat(guitar->sound(), Equals(sounds::clean));
</code></pre>
you can write<p><pre><code>  CHECK(guitar->sound() == sounds::clean);
</code></pre>
And you&#x27;ll still get sensible output when it fails, showing the expression and the result of guitar->sound().
